## ðŸ“š Official Scikit-learn Documentation

1. **TF-IDF Vectorizer**
   - Converts text documents into a matrix of TF-IDF features.
   - Documentation: TfidfVectorizer â€” Scikit-learn [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fgenerated%2Fsklearn.feature_extraction.text.TfidfVectorizer.html")  
   - Key parameters:
     - `stop_words`: remove common words (e.g., "english").
     - `ngram_range`: use unigrams, bigrams, etc.
     - `max_features`: limit vocabulary size.

2. **Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA)**
   - A generative probabilistic model for discovering topics in text.
   - Documentation: LatentDirichletAllocation â€” Scikit-learn [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fgenerated%2Fsklearn.decomposition.LatentDirichletAllocation.html")  
   - Key parameters:
     - `n_components`: number of topics.
     - `max_iter`: number of iterations for convergence.
     - `learning_method`: batch or online.
     - `random_state`: reproducibility.

3. **Model Evaluation**
   - LDA provides **perplexity** and **log-likelihood** as evaluation metrics.
   - Documentation: Evaluating LDA models [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fdecomposition.html%23latent-dirichlet-allocation")

